LCSD Facility Use Request and Reservation Management System
Product Requirements Document (PRD) for AI Implementation
Version: 1.0
Date: April 2026
AI Coding Assistant: Windsurf
Implementation Scope: Front-end prototype with simulated backend


1. SYSTEM OVERVIEW
1.1 Problem Statement: The Local County School District (LCSD) currently lacks a centralized system for managing after-hours and weekend facility use requests. This results in:
•	Miscommunication between requestors and administrative staff
•	Missed HVAC scheduling leading to energy waste
•	Lost contract renewals and revenue
•	Lack of accountability in the approval process
•	Difficulty tracking facility usage for reporting

1.2 System Purpose: The LCSD Facility Use Request and Reservation Management System ("The System") streamlines the management of all requests to use LCSD facilities after-hours and on weekends by:
•	Gathering standardized information from requestors
•	Routing requests through an approval workflow (Requestor → Principal → Operations → Calendar)
•	Providing a centralized calendar for monitoring scheduled activities
•	Generating quotes for paid facility use
•	Tracking HVAC, custodial, and maintenance requirements
•	Maintaining historical records for accountability

1.3 Key Stakeholders
•	Public Requestors: Community members requesting facility use
•	Employee Requestors: LCSD employees requesting facility use
•	Principals: Review and approve/deny requests for their schools
•	Operations Department Staff: Generate quotes, manage contracts
•	Energy Manager: Monitor HVAC usage and costs
•	LCSD Employees (General): View calendar and reference documents

1.4 System Scope
In Scope:
•	Centralized request submission (one-time and long-term events)
•	Multi-step approval workflow
•	Calendar view with filtering capabilities
•	Quote generation for paid contracts
•	Email notifications at key workflow points
•	Reference document library
•	Archived request access
•	HVAC/custodial/maintenance reporting
Out of Scope:
•	Automatic approval based on predefined rules
•	Direct HVAC system integration
•	Custom form builders for different event types
•	Event planning features (catering, equipment rental)
•	Payment processing
•	Real-time availability checking


