2.3 Data Retention & Business Rules
•	All reservation requests (approved, denied, quote-pending) retained for 5 years from event date
•	Denied requests immediately archived (removed from active calendar but retained in database)
•	Long-term contracts trigger 30-day expiration notification
•	Principals assigned to multiple schools: schools combined into single Location entity differentiated by Space
•	Operations Staff and Energy Manager: not assigned to specific schools (system-wide access)
•	Public users: cannot access calendar view
•	LCSD Employees: calendar filtered based on school associations (or all schools if none assigned)


3. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
3.1 Pre-Reservation Approval Support
•	FR-1.1: Request Submission The system shall allow Public Requestors and LCSD Employees to submit facility reservation requests for one-time or long-term events.
•	FR-1.2: Request Notification The system shall notify the appropriate Principal when a new request is submitted for their school.
•	FR-1.3: Calendar Access The system shall provide a calendar view showing pending and approved reservations.
•	FR-1.4: Quote Generation The system shall allow Operations Department Staff to generate quotes for long-term facility use by public requestors.
•	3.2 Post-Decision Support
•	FR-2.1: Approval/Denial Notification The system shall notify requestors when their request is approved or denied.
•	FR-2.2: Calendar Filtering The system shall allow LCSD Employees to filter calendar views by month/year, school, and status.
•	FR-2.3: Denial Handling The system shall archive denied requests and remove them from the active calendar.
•	FR-2.4: Contract Expiration Alerts The system shall notify requestors and administrators 30 days before long-term contract expiration.
•	3.3 Ongoing Support
•	FR-3.1: Calendar Access (Non-Administrative) The system shall allow LCSD Employees to view the calendar without modification rights.
•	FR-3.2: Historical Record Retention The system shall retain all reservation details for 5 years after the event date.
•	FR-3.3: Reference Document Access The system shall provide access to reference documents (guidelines, policies) for all users.
•	FR-3.4: Reporting The system shall allow Administrative Users to generate reports on HVAC usage, custodial support, and maintenance coverage.

4. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

•	NFR-1.1: The system shall run on computers, tablets, and cellular devices
•	NFR-1.2: The system shall be web-based and run on any modern browser
•	NFR-1.3: The system shall be available 24 hours per day, 365 days per year (conceptual)
•	NFR-1.4: The system event calendar shall visually differentiate between pending and approved events
•	NFR-1.5: The system shall conform to LCSD policies
•	NFR-1.6: The system shall include safeguards from security threats (conceptual)

5. DATA MODEL
5.1 Entity Definitions
The system manages six primary entities:
EVENT
Stores all facility reservation requests regardless of approval status.
Attributes:
•	EV_ID (Number, Primary Key): Unique identifier
•	EV_Frequency (Text): "One-time" or "Long-term"
•	EV_RequestorID (Number, Foreign Key): References USER_ID
•	EV_ReviewerID (Number, Foreign Key): USER_ID of last person to update status
•	EV_Organization (Text): Organization name associated with event
•	EV_OneTimeDate (Date): Date for one-time events
•	EV_LongTermStartDate (Date): Start date for recurring events
•	EV_LongTermEndDate (Date): End date for recurring events
•	EV_StartTime (Time): Event start time
•	EV_EndTime (Time): Event end time
•	EV_SchoolID (Number, Foreign Key): References SCH_ID
•	EV_SpaceID (Number, Foreign Key): References SPACE_ID
•	EV_Attendees (Number): Expected number of attendees
•	EV_Description (Text): Event description
•	EV_Custodial (Text): Requested custodial support details
•	EV_Maintenance (Text): Requested maintenance support details
•	EV_Files (File): Uploaded supporting documents
•	EV_Status (Text): "Pending", "Approved", "Quote Pending", "Quote Sent", "Denied"
•	EV_Comments (Text): Internal comments from Administrative Users
USER
Stores information about all individuals who interact with the system.
Attributes:
•	USER_ID (Number, Primary Key): Unique identifier
•	USER_Type (Text): "Public User", "LCSD Employee", "Principal", "Operations Department Staff", "Energy Manager"
•	USER_Name (Text): Full name
•	USER_Email (Text): Email address
•	USER_Phone (Text): Phone number (stored as text to preserve formatting)
•	USER_School (Text): Associated schools (can be multiple, null for system-wide users)
•	USER_Status (Text): "Active" or "Inactive"
SCHOOL
Stores information about LCSD schools that can host events.
Attributes:
•	SCH_ID (Number, Primary Key): Unique identifier
•	SCH_Name (Text): School name
•	SCH_Type (Text): "High School", "Middle School", "Elementary School", "K-12", "Special Programs"
•	SCH_StreetAddress (Text): Street address
•	SCH_City (Text): City name
•	SCH_Zip (Text): ZIP code (stored as text for leading zeros)
•	SCH_Status (Text): "Active" or "Inactive"
SPACE
Stores details about reservable spaces within schools.
Attributes:
•	SPACE_ID (Number, Primary Key): Unique identifier
•	SPACE_SchoolID (Number, Foreign Key): References SCH_ID
•	SPACE_Name (Text): Space name (e.g., "Gym", "Cafeteria", "Room 200")
•	SPACE_Capacity (Number): Maximum occupancy
•	SPACE_Status (Text): "Available" or "Unavailable"
QUOTE
Stores quote details for paid facility contracts.
Attributes:
•	QUOTE_ID (Number, Primary Key): Unique identifier
•	QUOTE_EventID (Number, Foreign Key): References EV_ID
•	QUOTE_CreatorID (Number, Foreign Key): USER_ID of Operations Staff who created quote
•	QUOTE_Custodial (Number): Amount for custodial services
•	QUOTE_Maintenance (Number): Amount for maintenance services
•	QUOTE_MiscFees (Number): Taxes, fees, etc.
•	QUOTE_Hourly (Number): Hourly facility use rate
•	QUOTE_Status (Text): "Pending", "Accepted", "Denied"
REFERENCE_DOCUMENT
Stores reference documents for system users.
Attributes:
•	DOC_ID (Number, Primary Key): Unique identifier
•	DOC_Name (Text): Document name
•	DOC_Status (Text): "Current" or "Archived"
•	DOC_UploaderID (Number, Foreign Key): USER_ID of administrator who uploaded
5.2 Entity Relationships
1.	User requests Event (one-to-many): One User can submit multiple Events
2.	User reviews Event (one-to-many): One User (reviewer) can review multiple Events (tracked via EV_ReviewerID)
3.	User creates Quote (one-to-many): One User (Operations Staff) can create multiple Quotes
4.	Quote is generated for Event (one-to-one): Each Quote is for exactly one Event
5.	School contains Space (one-to-many): One School contains multiple Spaces
6.	School hosts Event (one-to-many): One School can host multiple Events
7.	Space holds Event (one-to-many): One Space can hold multiple Events
8.	User is assigned to School (one-to-many): Users assigned to schools; some users (Operations, Energy Manager, Public) have null school assignment
9.	User uploads Reference Document (one-to-many): One User (admin) can upload multiple documents
Note on Multi-School Principals: Principals assigned to 2+ schools will have those schools combined into one School entity, differentiated by Space, to avoid many-to-many complexity.
