6. USE CASES
6.1 UC-Request 1: Public Requestor Submits One-Time Event Request
Primary Actor: Public Requestor
Preconditions: User accesses the system
Trigger: User clicks "Submit a Request"
Main Flow:
1.	System displays one-time vs. recurring event selection
2.	User selects "One-time event"
3.	System displays one-time event form fields
4.	User enters: contact name, organization, email, phone, date, start/end time, school, space, attendees, description, custodial/maintenance needs
5.	User optionally uploads supporting files (PDF, Word, Excel; max 10MB)
6.	User clicks "Submit"
7.	System validates all required fields and data formats
8.	System generates PDF confirmation
9.	System emails PDF to requestor
10.	System identifies Principal associated with requested school
11.	System emails Principal notification to review request
12.	System adds request to calendar with "Pending" status
13.	System displays confirmation message to user
Postconditions:
•	Event record created with status "Pending"
•	Requestor receives confirmation email
•	Principal receives review notification
•	Event appears on calendar as pending
Alternative Flows:
•	7a. Validation fails: System displays field-level error messages, user corrects and resubmits
6.2 UC-Request 2: Employee Requestor Submits Long-Term Event Request
Primary Actor: LCSD Employee Requestor
Preconditions: Employee accesses the system
Trigger: User clicks "Submit a Request"
Main Flow:
1.	System displays one-time vs. recurring event selection
2.	User selects "Long-term event"
3.	System displays long-term event form fields
4.	System auto-populates requestor name and email from employee profile
5.	User enters: organization, phone, start date, end date, start time, end time, school, space, attendees, description, custodial/maintenance needs
6.	User optionally uploads supporting files
7.	User clicks "Submit"
8.	System validates all required fields
9.	System generates PDF confirmation
10.	System emails PDF to requestor
11.	System identifies Principal for requested school
12.	System emails Principal notification
13.	System adds request to calendar with "Pending" status
14.	System displays confirmation message
Postconditions: Same as UC-Request 1
6.3 UC-Review 1: Principal Reviews and Approves One-Time Employee Request
Primary Actor: Principal
Preconditions: At least one pending request exists for Principal's school
Trigger: Principal clicks "Review Requests"
Main Flow:
1.	System displays list of pending requests for Principal's school(s)
2.	Principal selects a request to review
3.	System displays: 
o	Request details (all submitted information)
o	Calendar view showing month of requested event
o	Any uploaded files
o	Internal comment text field
4.	Principal reviews information
5.	Principal optionally enters internal comments
6.	Principal clicks "Approve"
7.	System saves comments (if entered)
8.	System updates event status to "Approved"
9.	System updates calendar event status to "Approved" (visually differentiated)
10.	System emails Requestor: approval notification
11.	System emails Operations Staff: event details, custodial/maintenance needs
12.	System emails Energy Manager: event details for HVAC scheduling
Postconditions:
•	Event status = "Approved"
•	Calendar shows event as approved
•	Requestor, Operations, and Energy Manager notified
Alternative Flows:
•	6a. Principal clicks "Deny": 
o	System updates status to "Denied"
o	System removes event from calendar
o	System archives request
o	System emails Requestor with denial notification (includes comments)
6.4 UC-Review 2: Principal Approves Long-Term Public Request for Quote
Primary Actor: Principal
Trigger: Principal reviews a long-term request from a public requestor
Main Flow: 
1-5. Same as UC-Review 1 
6.	Principal clicks "Approved for Quote" 
7.	System saves comments (if entered) 
8.	System updates event status to "Quote Pending" 
9.	System updates calendar to "Quote Pending" 
10.	System emails Operations Staff: request details and instructions to generate quote
Postconditions:
•	Event status = "Quote Pending"
•	Operations Staff receives quote generation request
6.5 UC-Review 3: Operations Staff Generates Quote
Primary Actor: Operations Department Staff Member
Preconditions: Request approved for quote generation
Trigger: Operations Staff opens quote generation request
Main Flow:
1.	System displays quote form pre-populated with: 
o	Requestor information
o	Event details
o	Standard rates for custodial, maintenance, hourly use
2.	Operations Staff reviews and adjusts rates if needed
3.	Operations Staff enters any additional fees or comments
4.	Operations Staff clicks "Send Quote"
5.	System validates quote details
6.	System updates event status to "Quote Sent"
7.	System generates PDF quote
8.	System emails quote to Requestor and Principal
Postconditions:
•	Quote record created
•	Event status = "Quote Sent"
•	Requestor and Principal receive quote
Alternative Flows:
•	4a. Operations Staff denies request: 
o	System updates status to "Denied"
o	System removes from calendar
o	System archives request
o	System notifies Requestor and Principal
6.6 UC-Calendar 1: LCSD Employee Views Calendar
Primary Actor: LCSD Employee
Trigger: Employee clicks "View Calendar"
Main Flow:
1.	System determines employee's school associations
2.	If employee assigned to one school: 
o	System displays calendar for that school
3.	If employee assigned to multiple schools: 
o	System displays calendar for all assigned schools
4.	If employee not assigned to any school (Operations, Energy Manager): 
o	System displays calendar for all schools
5.	System shows events with: 
o	Event dates and times
o	Event locations
o	Event status (Pending or Approved - visually differentiated by color/icon)
6.	System displays filter controls: 
o	Month/Year selector (default: current month)
o	School dropdown (if user has multiple schools)
o	Status filter: Pending, Approved, All (default: All)
Postconditions: Calendar displayed with appropriate events
6.7 UC-Calendar 2: LCSD Employee Filters Calendar
Primary Actor: LCSD Employee
Preconditions: Calendar is displayed
Trigger: Employee updates filter selections
Main Flow:
1.	Employee selects filter parameters (month/year, school, status)
2.	System refreshes calendar to display only events matching filters
3.	Filter selections persist during current session only
Postconditions: Calendar shows filtered view
6.8 UC-Documentation 1: User Reviews Reference Documents
Primary Actor: Any User (Public, Employee, Administrative)
Trigger: User clicks "Reference Documents"
Main Flow:
1.	System displays list of current reference documents
2.	User selects a document to view
3.	System opens document in new browser tab
Postconditions: User has access to reference information
6.9 UC-Documentation 2: Administrative User Reviews Archived Requests
Primary Actor: Administrative User
Trigger: Admin clicks "Archived Requests"
Main Flow:
1.	System displays list of archived requests (past 5 years)
2.	System displays pagination controls if needed
3.	Admin selects a request to view
4.	System displays complete request details (read-only)
Postconditions: Admin has viewed historical request
6.10 UC-Reporting 1: Administrative User Generates Report
Primary Actor: Energy Manager, Operations Staff, or Principal
Trigger: User clicks "Generate Report" from Calendar View
Main Flow:
1.	System displays report parameter popup: 
o	Report type: HVAC Usage, Custodial Support, Maintenance Coverage
o	Date range selector
o	School selector (if applicable)
2.	User selects parameters
3.	User clicks "Generate"
4.	System compiles data based on parameters
5.	System displays/downloads report
Postconditions: User has report for analysis
