9. ERROR HANDLING & VALIDATION
9.1 Input Validation
Field-Level Validation: All input fields have associated data types and validation rules. Validation occurs on field blur (when user leaves field) and on form submission.
Data Type Validation:
Data Type	Validation Rules	Error Message
Text	Max length, required if specified	"This field is required" or "Maximum [X] characters"
Email	Must contain @ and ., valid format	"Please enter a valid email address"
Phone	Format: (XXX) XXX-XXXX	"Phone must be in format (XXX) XXX-XXXX"
Number	Must be integer, positive if specified	"Please enter a valid number"
Date	Valid date, future date if required	"Please select a valid date" or "Date must be in the future"
Time	Valid time, logical time range	"End time must be after start time"
File	Type: .pdf, .doc, .docx, .xls, .xlsx; Size: max 10MB	"Invalid file type" or "File size exceeds 10MB"
Form-Level Validation: When user attempts to submit a form, system checks:
1.	All required fields are filled
2.	All field-level validations pass
3.	Logical consistency (e.g., end date after start date)
If validation fails:
•	Display error summary at top of form: "Please correct the errors below"
•	Highlight invalid fields with red border
•	Display specific error message below each invalid field
•	Scroll to first invalid field
•	Do not allow form submission
If validation succeeds:
•	Remove all error messages
•	Allow form submission to proceed
9.2 User Feedback
Real-Time Validation:
•	Field-level errors appear when user leaves field (on blur event)
•	Error disappears when user corrects the field
•	Visual indicators: red border, red text, error icon
Submission Feedback:
•	Loading indicator while processing
•	Success message: Green alert box with checkmark icon
•	Error message: Red alert box with X icon
